    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.10.19" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">19</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">UPTON SINCLAIR
                        <lb/>
                    PASADENA
                        <lb/>
                    CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Sept. 21, 1923.</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Bancroft, Neb.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Friend:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I understand that you are to be in Southern California shortly. This is to advise you that I have been working for the last four months to put the American Civil Librerties Union on its feet; we have a salaried director, and we are, among other activities, conducting an open forum every Sunday evening.</p>
                
                <p>Will you contribute your services for a three-quarters of an hour talk, after which the audience will ask you questions? At the present stage of our development, we cannot pay anybody except for the director, who gives all his time. It is a contribution to the cause. Please let me know as soon as possible when you expect to be in Los Angeles.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>U Sinclair</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
